==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Decennary
<hw>De*cen"na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Decennaries</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>decennium</ets>
a period of ten years; <ets>decem</ets> ten + <ets>annus</ets> a
year.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A period of ten years.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A tithing consisting of ten
neighboring families.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decennial</ent>⟦br⟧
